<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Source Entry</div>
<dl id="TT1904"> <dt><sauthor></sauthor> <stitle><cite>The Times</cite></stitle> (London: June 1904). </dt> <dd> <ul> <li>Original index: UN2, pp 3-23 </li> <li>Sample use: <a name="un2003a" href="../unbs/un2all.htm#un2003a">UN2 (VI.D.7):003(a)</a> </li> <li>Raphael copy: VI.C.16 232-247 </li> <li>Publication: James Joyce, <cite>The Lost Notebook</cite>, ed. Danis Rose and John O&apos;Hanlon, (Edinburgh: Split Pea Press, 1989). </li> <li>Identified by: Danis Rose and John O&apos;Hanlon </li> <li>For his recreation of Bloomsday, Joyce read through the back numbers of this newspaper (historic Irish newspapers not being available in war-time Zurich) starting with the 17 June 1904 issue and ending with 1 June 1904. </li></ul> </dd> </dl>
